It is highly recommended that you speak to your doctor before making any drastic changes to your diet and activity levels. When speaking with a doctor, it's important to express your concerns about your overall health and wellness. Before starting a new exercise plan or diet, it's crucial to talk to your doctor. Ask the doctor to explain your body fat percentage and recommended caloric intake based on your age, height, and weight. Request clarification on how to maintain a healthy body fat percentage through diet and ask for specific tips, such as recommended foods and portion sizes, or general advice on making healthy food choices. It's also important to discuss your exercise plan with your doctor to ensure it is safe and appropriate for your health needs. Thank the doctor for their time and support, and inquire if there's anything else you should be aware of regarding your health and wellness. </p>
